  "text": "Filter definition depends on data characteristics and the purpose of the analysis. As with other topological techniques, density estimates, centrality functions, orthogonal coordinates, a subset of dimensions and intermediate algorithmic results [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] are also supported in STAD. The inclusion of filters aims to enrich data exploration through explicit prior knowledge [CITATION_3] rather than hypothesis-free research. In practice, subsets of dimensions or external data tend to be most interpretable.",
